## Part 1: Strategic Foundation

### 1.1 Executive Summary

- **Mission:** Create a unified, portable compliance credential system for heavy vehicle drivers and operators across Australia.
- **Vision:** Eliminate duplicated training requirements while maintaining the highest safety standards across freight receiving sites.
- **Current status (March 2026):** Operational newsletter platform (CoR Intel Weekly + Safe Freight Mate) actively building industry audience. Commercial credential platform in development.
- **Market opportunity:** 250,000+ heavy vehicle drivers requiring compliance training; major receivers seeking efficient verification systems.

### 1.2 Business Model

**Current phase — Audience Building (Free)**
- CoR Intel Weekly: professional compliance intelligence for transport stakeholders
- Safe Freight Mate: driver-focused safety and regulatory updates
- Purpose: establish credibility, build subscriber base, validate market demand before commercial launch

**Commercial Platform (Planned)**
- Driver Passport Subscriptions — $99/year portable compliance credential
- Receiver Verification Services — $399–$1,299/month per site
- AIL Partnership Revenue — accreditation fees + inspection revenue share
- Trainer Partnership Revenue — certification fees, 65/35 revenue split

### 1.3 Market Position

- Only dedicated Chain of Responsibility intelligence service in Australia
- No direct newsletter competitors in the CoR compliance space
- First mover advantage in unified digital credential platform
- NHVR relationship: neutral-to-positive; no regulatory barriers identified

