## Part 2: Newsletter Products

### 2.1 CoR Intel Weekly (Pro Segment)

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Audience | Compliance managers, transport executives, safety professionals, legal/risk professionals |
| Tone | Professional, analytical, strategic. Never speculative on enforcement outcomes. |
| Category priority | Regulatory Update → Enforcement Action → Regulatory Guidance → Safety Alert → From the Industry |
| Min score thresholds | Compliance slot: 72+. Industry slot: 65+ |
| Article count | 2–4 articles (quality-first, not fixed 5 slots) |
| Action tips | Specific to duty-holder obligations. No "contact your legal team" speculation. |

### 2.2 Safe Freight Mate (Driver Segment)

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Audience | Heavy vehicle drivers, owner-operators |
| Tone | Conversational, plain English, supportive. "Servo talk" voice for industry slot. |
| Category priority | Road Intel/Intercepts → Fatigue/Hours → Driver Wellness → Safety Alert → Servo Talk |
| Min score thresholds | Road Intel slot: 68+. Servo Talk slot: 63+ |
| Wellbeing content | Synthesised SFP original content acceptable when no external source passes threshold |
| Action tips | Practical, specific. No victim-blaming. No "check with your employer" deflection. |

### 2.3 Content Sources (Active — March 2026)

| Source | Type | Segments |
|--------|------|----------|
| NHVR Latest News | Direct HTML scrape | Pro + Driver |
| NHVR On the Road | Direct HTML scrape | Pro + Driver |
| NHVR Safety Alerts | Direct HTML scrape | Pro + Driver |
| NHVR Consultations | Direct HTML scrape | Pro |
| NHVR Publications | Direct HTML scrape (PDF filtered) | Pro |
| ATA (Australian Trucking Association) | RSS with compliance keyword filter | Pro + Driver |
| JADE court decisions | RSS (transport cases only) | Pro |
| ATN / Big Rigs / Owner Driver | RSS | Pro + Driver |
| SafeWork NSW | RSS (heavy vehicle keywords only) | Pro + Driver |
| TWU | RSS (excludes aviation and unrelated content) | Driver |

### 2.4 Content Filtering Principles

**Always excluded regardless of source:**
- Pure advocacy/lobbying (fuel tax, road user charges, "calls for government action")
- Market/sales/financial news (truck sales figures, company earnings, market share)
- Conference registrations, awards, Australia Day honours
- Traffic alerts, roadworks, night works (not compliance-relevant)
- University research without direct operational implication
- Fatal crashes in the industry/servo talk slot
- PDF filenames accidentally scraped from publications listing pages
- Peak body welcome statements ("welcomes funding announcement" etc.)

**Diversity caps:**
- Maximum 3 Regulatory Update articles per Pro newsletter
- Industry/Servo Talk slot uses a separate GPT pass with conversational rewrite
- 21-day recency filter on articles (configurable)

**Geographic scoring:**
- NHVR sources receive +5 base relevance bonus
- Foreign content penalised
- Australian operational focus maintained

