## Part 3: Technical Infrastructure

### 3.1 System Architecture

```
Content Sources (RSS + HTML scraping)
          ↓
Railway Node.js Server  (/app/src/index.js — Express API)
          ↓                          ↓
    scraper.js               generator.js  (OpenAI GPT-4o)
          ↓                          ↓
  Google Sheets DB          emailSender.js  (Resend API)
    Article_Archive            Subscribers sheet
    Schedule_Config                  ↓
    Events_Log              Newsletter_Archive (planned)
                                     ↓
                    newsletter-management.html  (Admin Dashboard)
                    advancedScheduler.js  (Cron automation)
```

### 3.2 Repository Structure

```
/
├── src/
│   ├── index.js                ← Express server + all API routes
│   ├── generator.js            ← Newsletter generation (OpenAI GPT-4o)
│   ├── emailSender.js          ← Resend API sending + subscriber fetching
│   ├── scraper.js              ← Content scraping engine
│   └── advancedScheduler.js   ← node-cron scheduling system
├── config/
│   ├── sheets.js               ← All Google Sheets read/write methods
│   └── config.js               ← Env var wrappers + scraping source list
├── public/
│   └── newsletter-management.html   ← Admin dashboard (static SPA)
├── package.json
└── railway.toml
```

> **⚠️ CRITICAL PATH NOTE**
> `index.js` is at `/app/src/index.js` on Railway.
> `sheets.js` is at `/app/config/sheets.js` — **NOT** in `src/`.
> All `require()` calls to sheets must use `'../config/sheets'` (not `'./sheets'`).
> This applies in: `index.js`, `generator.js`, `advancedScheduler.js`.
> `generator.js` also uses `require('../config/config')` — also correct.

### 3.3 Key Files

| File | Purpose | Key Notes |
|------|---------|-----------|
| `src/index.js` | Express server. All API endpoints. Scheduler wiring. Basic Auth middleware. | ~1,425 lines (v3.1). Contains `getAllSubscribersFromSheet()`, admin subscriber routes, analytics endpoints, system state tracking, `getSheetsClient()` centralised helper. |
| `src/generator.js` | OpenAI newsletter generation for both segments | Calls `sheetsManager.getRecentArticles()`, builds HTML template, calls `emailSender.sendNewsletter()`. Quality-first: min score thresholds, not fixed slots. |
| `src/emailSender.js` | Resend API email sending. Subscriber fetching for sends. | `getSubscribersFromSheet()` filters to `active`/`confirmed`/`subscribed` only. Reads `Subscribers!A:R`. Injects unsubscribe/pause tokens per email. |
| `src/scraper.js` | Article scraping from all configured sources | Source config lives in `config/config.js`. Handles RSS + direct HTML. Writes to Article_Archive sheet. |
| `src/advancedScheduler.js` | node-cron scheduling for scraping + newsletter jobs | Timezone: `Australia/Sydney`. `onJobComplete` callback wired for Events_Log. Config loaded from Google Sheets `Schedule_Config` tab on startup. |
| `config/sheets.js` | All Google Sheets read/write operations | Methods: `getRecentArticles`, `saveArticles`, `markArticlesAsUsed`, `getSubscriberByEmail`, `updateSubscriberByEmail`, `getAuth`. Uses `googleapis`. |
| `config/config.js` | Env var exports + full scraping source list | `config.openai.apiKey`, `config.sheets.spreadsheetId`, `config.sources[]`. |
| `public/newsletter-management.html` | Admin dashboard SPA | Served at `/newsletter-management`. Tabs: Operations, Subscribers, Schedule, Analytics, Settings. Protected by Basic Auth. |

