## Part 4: Google Sheets Database Schema

### 4.1 Subscribers Sheet (`Subscribers`)

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Subscriber_ID` | `SUB-{timestamp}` generated on creation |
| `Email` | Lowercase email address |
| `Name` | Display name |
| `Segment` | Comma-separated: `pro`, `driver`, or `pro,driver` |
| `Status` | `pending` / `active` / `paused` / `unsubscribed` |
| `Subscribed_At` | UTC ISO timestamp of signup |
| `Confirmed_At` | UTC ISO timestamp of email confirmation or admin activation |
| `Unsubscribed_At` | UTC ISO timestamp if unsubscribed (blank = still subscribed) |
| `Unsub_Token` | 16-char hex token for unsubscribe/pause links |
| `Confirm_Token` | 16-char hex token for email confirmation (public signup only) |
| `Company` | Optional |
| `Role` | Optional |
| `Paused_At` | Set by `/api/pause`; cleared when `Resume_At` passes |
| `Resume_At` | UTC ISO timestamp when newsletters should resume |
| `Updated_At` | UTC ISO timestamp of last modification |

> **STATUS RULES for email sending:**
> `emailSender.getSubscribersFromSheet()` sends ONLY to: `active`, `confirmed`, `subscribed`
> `pending` subscribers do NOT receive newsletters.
> Admin dashboard shows ALL statuses — use Activate button to promote pending → active.
> Admin-added subscribers (`/api/admin/subscriber`) are set `active` immediately.
> Public subscribe form (`/api/subscribers`) sets `pending` + sends confirmation email.

### 4.2 Subscriber Segment Management

The subscriber record stores segment as a single comma-separated field (e.g. `pro,driver`). As of v3.1, the `PUT /api/subscribers/:email` endpoint accepts segment as a comma-separated string, single value, or array, and normalises to canonical order (`pro` before `driver`). To remove one segment, update to just `pro` or `driver`. To add both, update to `pro,driver`.

A proper per-subscription junction table model remains future work.

### 4.3 Article_Archive Sheet

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `ID` | Unique article ID |
| `Date_Collected` | UTC ISO timestamp of scrape (displays as Sydney time in dashboard) |
| `Source` | Source name from config (e.g. `NHVR Latest News`) |
| `Title` | Article title |
| `URL` | Source URL |
| `Published_Date` | Publication date from RSS `pubDate` or HTML `<time>` element |
| `Summary` | RSS summary or auto-generated |
| `Used_In_Issue` | Issue ID if article has been included in a sent newsletter |
| `Content_Hash` | MD5 hash for deduplication |
| `Relevance_Score` | Calculated relevance score |
| `Segment_Tag` | `pro`, `driver`, or `both` |

### 4.4 Events_Log Sheet

Tracks all system events. Used to populate "last scraped/sent" display in dashboard Operations tab.

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Timestamp` | UTC ISO timestamp |
| `Event_Type` | `scrape_completed`, `newsletter_sent`, `trigger` |
| `Issue_ID` | Issue identifier if newsletter event |
| `Segment` | `pro`, `driver`, or `scraping` |
| `Status` | `success` or `error` |
| `Trigger` | `manual` or `scheduled` |
| `Details` | JSON string with counts, errors, article IDs, etc. |

### 4.5 Send_Log Sheet

Per-send records including Resend IDs for engagement analytics.

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Sent_At` | UTC ISO timestamp |
| `Segment` | `pro` or `driver` |
| `Sent_Count` | Number of emails sent |
| `Failed_Count` | Number of send failures |
| `Engagement_Fetched` | `true` once Resend engagement has been pulled for this issue |
| `Notes` | JSON: `issue_id`, `subject`, `resend_ids[]`, `article_count` |

### 4.6 Schedule_Config Sheet *(new in v3.1)*

Stores schedule configuration so it survives Railway redeploys. Two rows, two columns.

| Column A (Key) | Column B (Value) |
|----------------|-----------------|
| `scraping` | JSON object: `{frequency, dayOfWeek, hour, minute, enabled, ...}` |
| `newsletter` | JSON object: `{frequency, dayOfWeek, hour, minute, enabled, delayAfterDependency, ...}` |

> **Setup required:** Create this tab manually in Google Sheets before first deploy. Leave it empty — it will be populated on first Save from the dashboard.

### 4.7 Subscriber_Audit Sheet

Immutable audit trail for subscriber changes (deletes, status changes, admin edits).

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Timestamp` | UTC ISO |
| `Action` | `deleted`, `paused`, `unsubscribed`, `activated`, `edited` |
| `Email` | Subscriber email |
| `Metadata` | JSON with subscriber details at time of action |
| `IP` | Request IP if available |
| `User_Agent` | Browser/client UA if available |

### 4.8 Newsletter_Archive Sheet *(planned — not yet implemented)*

Will store full HTML of every sent newsletter for record-keeping and re-send capability. See Part 11.

