## Part 6: Admin Dashboard

### 6.1 Overview

Single-file SPA at `https://www.safefreightprogram.com/newsletter-management`. All state loaded via `fetch()` to the Railway API. Protected by HTTP Basic Auth (set `ADMIN_USER`/`ADMIN_PASS` Railway env vars).

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| URL | `https://www.safefreightprogram.com/newsletter-management` |
| Railway backend | `https://sfp-newsletter-automation-production.up.railway.app` |
| Auth | HTTP Basic Auth — browser prompts for username/password |

### 6.2 Tabs

**Operations Tab**
- Run Scraping — calls `POST /api/scrape`
- Newsletter Workflow — select segment → Generate Preview (renders HTML in right panel) → Send to all subscribers
- Test Email — sends to specified address
- Last scraped/sent — shows CoR Intel and Safe Freight Mate separately with `(manual)`/`(scheduled)` qualifier

**Subscribers Tab**
- Subscriber overview tiles (CoR Intel Weekly / Safe Freight Mate active counts)
- Subscriber table — shows ALL statuses including pending
- Pending subscribers show an **Activate** button
- Add Subscriber — form POSTs to `/api/admin/subscriber` (active immediately, no confirmation email)
- Edit / Delete buttons per row
- Segment filter dropdown, Refresh, Download CSV

**Schedule Tab**
- Left panel: Content Scraping and Newsletter Generation status cards (Active/Enabled, Frequency, Schedule, Next Run, Last Run, Trigger Now button)
- Right panel: Railway Schedule Configuration — Content Scraping / Newsletter tabs with Frequency/Day/Hour/Minute selectors
- Dependency Configuration: Newsletter waits for scraping + configurable additional delay (0–120 min)
- Save Schedule → updates Railway in-memory config. Must also click Save to Sheets (or call `POST /api/schedule/save-to-sheets`) to persist across deploys.

**Analytics Tab**
- Send metrics: total emails sent, success rate, issues tracked
- Engagement section with Refresh Engagement button (calls Resend API)
- Recent Issues table

### 6.3 Important Behavioural Notes

> - **Trigger Now** returns "triggered successfully" immediately — job runs async in background. Check Railway logs to confirm completion and email delivery.
> - **Subscriber table empty despite stats showing counts** = subscriber status is `pending`. Click Activate.
> - **Schedule not persisting across deploys** = you saved in the UI (updates `/tmp`) but didn't call `POST /api/schedule/save-to-sheets`. Do both after any schedule change.
> - **Emails appear sent but not received** — check Resend dashboard for delivery status and check junk/spam folder (especially Hotmail which is aggressive).
> - **Last scraped/sent times** come from Events_Log sheet, not in-memory state. They survive restarts.
> - **Auth prompt not appearing** = `ADMIN_USER`/`ADMIN_PASS` env vars not set in Railway. Auth is disabled until they are set.

