## Part 7: Subscription & Lifecycle Flow

### 7.1 Public Subscribe Flow

URL: `https://www.safefreightprogram.com/subscribe`

1. User selects edition(s) on subscribe.html — edition cards with expand/collapse detail
2. Submits form → `POST /api/subscribers` → `status = pending`, confirmation email sent
3. User clicks confirm link → `GET /api/confirm?token=` → `status = active`
4. Redirected to subscribe-confirmed.html
5. Receives newsletters at next scheduled or triggered send

### 7.2 Admin Add Subscriber Flow

1. Dashboard Subscribers tab → Add Subscriber
2. Fill name, email, segment(s)
3. `POST /api/admin/subscriber` → `status = active` immediately
4. Subscriber appears in table as active and will receive next send

### 7.3 Pause Flow

1. Subscriber clicks "Pause newsletters" link in email footer
2. `GET /api/pause?token=` → sets `Paused_At` + `Resume_At` (28 days) in sheet
3. `emailSender.getSubscribersFromSheet()` skips paused subscribers until `Resume_At` passes
4. Redirected to pause confirmation page

### 7.4 Unsubscribe Flow

1. Subscriber clicks "Unsubscribe" or "Email unsubscribe" in email footer
2. `GET /api/unsubscribe?token=&segment=` → sets `Unsubscribed_At` in sheet
3. `segment=all` removes from all; `segment=pro`/`driver` removes from that segment only
4. Subscriber record retained for audit; emails cease immediately

### 7.5 Required Email Footer Links

| Link Text | Endpoint |
|-----------|----------|
| Pause newsletters | `/api/pause?token={unsub_token}` |
| Unsubscribe | `/api/unsubscribe?token={unsub_token}&segment=all` |
| Email unsubscribe (segment-specific) | `/api/unsubscribe?token={unsub_token}&segment={segment}` |

