## Part 8: Known Issues, Decisions & Gotchas

### 8.1 Resolved Issues (as of March 2026)

| Issue | Resolution |
|-------|-----------|
| `Cannot find module './sheets'` error on Railway | `config/sheets.js` lives at `/app/config/`, not `/app/src/`. All requires must use `'../config/sheets'`. |
| `schedule-config.json` wiped on Railway redeploy | Resolved in v3.1 — config now persists to `Schedule_Config` Google Sheets tab. No longer depends on `/tmp`. |
| Subscriber table empty despite stats showing counts | `getSubscribersFromSheet()` for sends only returns `active`. Admin-added subscribers were `pending`. Fixed: `/api/subscribers` GET returns all statuses for dashboard. Admin add sets `active` immediately. |
| Trigger Now shows success but no emails arrive | Subscriber was `pending` at trigger time → sends to nobody. Resolved by activating subscriber first. |
| Edit subscriber returns `Cannot find module` | Same `config/sheets.js` path issue — resolved. |
| Sheet timestamps showing "wrong" timezone | Correct behaviour. Server runs UTC, stores UTC ISO strings. Dashboard displays Sydney time. Raw sheet shows UTC — expected. |
| No auth on admin dashboard | Resolved in v3.1 — Basic Auth middleware implemented. Activate by setting `ADMIN_USER`/`ADMIN_PASS` Railway env vars. |
| Segment editing fragile | Resolved in v3.1 — `PUT /api/subscribers/:email` now accepts CSV string, single value, or array. Canonical normalisation applied. |

### 8.2 Active Known Limitations

- **Newsletter archive not implemented** — sent newsletter HTML is not stored. Resend has delivery records but full content is not preserved server-side. See Part 11.
- **No site admin portal** — website Firebase auth exists for the subscriber-facing portal, but there is no admin UI for managing drivers/vehicles/AILs. See Part 11.
- **Website homepage mobile layout** — known responsive display issues on small screens. See Part 11.
- **Analytics engagement data limited by Resend plan** — free tier has limited event history window.
- **Article_Archive grows unboundedly** — no archival or purge mechanism implemented yet.
- **NHVR Publications** — can still scrape PDF filenames if the page structure changes. Monitor output.
- **Per-subscription metadata** — segment is still a single CSV field per subscriber record. Junction table model is future work.

### 8.3 Editorial Decisions (Locked)

- Quality-first over quantity — 2–4 articles with min score thresholds preferred over forced 5-slot fill
- Action tips: specific and operational. Banned phrases include "consult your legal team", "check with your employer", "contact your supervisor" as the primary tip
- Industry/Servo Talk slot: separate GPT pass with conversational rewrite, not compliance tone
- Driver Wellness: SFP can synthesise original content when no external source passes threshold — acceptable but label as own content
- Geographic scoring: NHVR sources get +5 base bonus. Foreign content penalised.
- 21-day recency filter active — articles older than 3 weeks excluded from selection pool
- Advocacy and lobbying content always excluded regardless of source or keyword match

