### A.3 Troubleshooting Cheatsheet

| Symptom | First Check |
|---------|-------------|
| Subscriber table empty despite stats showing counts | Status is `pending`. Use Activate button or `POST /api/admin/subscriber/activate`. |
| Trigger Now shows success but no email in inbox | Check Resend dashboard for delivery. Check junk/spam. Subscriber may have been `pending` at trigger time. |
| `Cannot find module './sheets'` | Require path is wrong. Must be `'../config/sheets'` from any file in `src/`. |
| Schedule config lost after redeploy | Call `POST /api/schedule/save-to-sheets` after saving schedule. Confirm `Schedule_Config` tab exists in Google Sheet. |
| Auth prompt not appearing on dashboard | `ADMIN_USER`/`ADMIN_PASS` not set in Railway env vars. Auth is disabled until both are set. |
| Newsletter sends to 0 people | No active subscribers OR Google Sheets API credentials failing (check Railway env vars). |
| Articles scraped but not appearing in newsletter | Check 21-day filter, relevance score thresholds, `Used_In_Issue` column (may already be used). |
| Email footer links 404 | Check `PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` env var is set to the Railway backend URL. |
| Dashboard shows "Connected to Railway" but table is stale | Click Refresh in the relevant tab. Dashboard data is not live-streaming — it fetches on demand. |

